Embattled eThekwini Mayor, Zandile Gumede has spoken for the first since her court appearance in the Durban Commercial Crimes Court over fraud charges. JOHANNESBURG - Beleaguered eThekwini Mayor and ANC regional chair Zandile Gumede is adamant she won't be fired. Gumede met with ANC officials in Durban on Sunday to discuss her fate. Speculation is rife that she’ll soon be recalled or placed on special leave – as she has been criminally charged for fraud and corruption. Gumede spoke exclusively to eNCA after meeting with ANC provincial structures. This after she was released on bail following a brief appearance in the Durban Commercial Crimes Court over multi-million rand fraud charges. READ: eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede out on bail "I'm so fortunate that I'm one of the leaders of this glorious movement of which everything is done through protocols. Today we had a good meeting with officials and they want to understand what happened," said Gumede. Asked whether she has been sacked? READ: More woes for eThekwini Mayor Zandile Gumede Gumede replied; "No, there's no such thing... as media you must learn to take from the horse’s mouth as you're doing today. For now, I've met with leaders and I went to court and then that's it". There have been calls for the beleaguered mayor to step aside.